---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About Last Season - The Football Season Archive"
  description="How Last Season is building a transparent, interactive archive of completed football seasons."
  canonical="/about/"
>
  <div class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><span class="current">About</span></nav>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <h1>About Last Season</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A football archive designed for exploration, comparison and reuse.</p>
    </section>
    <article class="prose section">
      <p>Last Season collects completed football-season records and turns them into readable tables, club histories and interactive tools. The aim is to answer specific historical questions quickly while making the underlying scope visible.</p>
      <h2>What the archive covers</h2>
      <p>Coverage varies by competition. Premier League coverage is currently the deepest; several other leagues contain a smaller verified range. A page only counts a season that is explicitly configured for publication.</p>
      <h2>What the archive does not claim</h2>
      <p>Player and club totals describe records present in this archive. They are not automatically complete all-competition career totals. Kit pages are currently colour studies based on broad historical eras, not authenticated shirt records.</p>
      <h2>Independence</h2>
      <p>Last Season is independent and is not affiliated with any league, club or governing body. Names and statistics are used for editorial and informational purposes.</p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions, corrections and partnership enquiries can be sent to <a href="mailto:hello@lastseason.co.uk">hello@lastseason.co.uk</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
